```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name example.com;
    root /var/www/html;
}
```
**server** block defines a virtual host. Each server block listens on specific ports and responds to specific domain names.

```nginx
upstream backend {
    server 10.0.0.1:8080;
    server 10.0.0.2:8080;
}
```
**upstream** defines a group of backend servers for load balancing. Default method is round-robin.

```nginx
listen 80;
listen 443 ssl;
listen [::]:80;
```
**listen** sets the address and port. Supports IPv4, IPv6, SSL, and HTTP/2.

```nginx
location /api {
    proxy_pass http://backend:3000;
}
```
**proxy_pass** forwards requests to a backend server (reverse proxy). The URL can be an upstream name or direct address.

```nginx
ssl_certificate /etc/letsencrypt/live/example.com/fullchain.pem;
ssl_certificate_key /etc/letsencrypt/live/example.com/privkey.pem;
```
**SSL certificate** directives specify the public certificate and private key for HTTPS.

```nginx
location / {
    try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html;
}
```
**try_files** checks for file existence in order. Commonly used for SPA fallback routing.

```nginx
gzip on;
gzip_types text/plain text/css application/json;
gzip_min_length 1000;
```
**gzip** enables response compression. Reduces bandwidth but uses CPU. Set gzip_types for which MIME types to compress.

```nginx
limit_req_zone $binary_remote_addr zone=api:10m rate=10r/s;
limit_req zone=api burst=20 nodelay;
```
**Rate limiting** restricts request rates per client IP. burst allows temporary spikes. nodelay processes burst immediately.

```nginx
add_header X-Frame-Options SAMEORIGIN;
add_header X-Content-Type-Options nosniff;
add_header Strict-Transport-Security "max-age=31536000";
```
**add_header** adds security and custom headers to responses.
